 ```
 
+### Draft for Review Only
+
+When the user asks you to draft a text/iMessage but not send it, use the bundled review-only helper. It opens Messages.app with a prefilled compose draft and has no send path.
+
+```bash
+python skills/apple/imessage/scripts/review_draft.py \
+  --to "+141****1212" \
+  --text "Draft this, but let me review before sending."
+
+# Validation / preview mode: prints the Messages URL without opening Messages.app.
+python skills/apple/imessage/scripts/review_draft.py \
+  --to "+141****1212" \
+  --text "Draft this, but let me review before sending." \
+  --print-url
+```
+
 ### Send Messages
 
 ```bash
 # Text only
-imsg send --to "+14155551212" --text "Hello!"
+imsg send --to "+141****1212" --text "Hello!"
 
 # With attachment
-imsg send --to "+14155551212" --text "Check this out" --file /path/to/image.jpg
+imsg send --to "+141****1212" --text "Check this out" --file /path/to/image.jpg
 
 # Force iMessage or SMS
-imsg send --to "+14155551212" --text "Hi" --service imessage
-imsg send --to "+14155551212" --text "Hi" --service sms
+imsg send --to "+141****1212" --text "Hi" --service imessage
+imsg send --to "+141****1212" --text "Hi" --service sms
 ```
 
 ### Watch for New Messages
